🚀 Concepts Covered

Understanding categorical variables

Ordinal Encoding --Ordinal Encoding is used for feature columns (X).

Label Encoding -- Label Encoding is mainly used for the target variable (y).

When to use each encoding technique

Converting categorical data into numerical format for ML models

🔹 Ordinal Encoding

Ordinal Encoding is used when categorical values have a meaningful order or ranking.

Example:
Education Level → School < College < Postgraduate

Here, the order matters, so encoding should preserve this hierarchy.

🔹 Label Encoding

Label Encoding is used when categorical values do not have any logical order.

Example:
Colors → Red, Blue, Green

In this case, numbers are just labels and do not represent ranking.

🧠 Why This is Important

Machine learning models cannot understand text-based categorical values.
Encoding helps convert these categories into numerical form so models can process them.

Choosing the correct encoding technique improves:

Model performance

Data interpretation

Feature representation
